","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Patients can manage their appointments directly through the portal or mobile app. Clinics stay in control, with the option to confirm rescheduling requests. If the clinic needs to reschedule an appointment, patients can confirm it from their end."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What happens when a patient cancels a paid appointment?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When a cancellation occurs, the payment is refunded as credits into the patient's wallet within the system. Patients can use these credits for future bookings, while providers avoid payment gateway refund hassles."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can appointments be linked to services and multiple clinic locations?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Appointments are mapped to the services you offer—such as in-person and telehealth consultations—and can be tied to the correct provider and location across multi-branch clinics."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can patients manage their appointments from a portal or mobile app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can log into their secure account online or via the mobile app to book, reschedule, cancel, and view their appointment history at any time. They can also confirm any rescheduling initiated by the clinic."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do automated reminders reduce no-shows?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The system sends patients timely confirmations and reminders by email, SMS, or in-app notifications. Providers also receive daily digests of upcoming appointments. This helps reduce no-shows and keeps schedules on track."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does appointment scheduling connect with consultation documentation and records?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Once an appointment is completed, providers can generate consultation notes, prescriptions, lab orders, and visit summaries. Patients receive secure access to the records t